ðŸ›  Steps to Perform Kubernetes Security Scan with Kubescape



1. Install Kubescape



On your local machine:



curl -s https://raw.githubusercontent.com/kubescape/kubescape/master/install.sh | /bin/bash



Verify installation:



kubescape version





---



2. Install a Local K8s Cluster



Choose one (for testing, Kind is lightweight):



# Kind

kind create cluster --name k8s-sec-scan



or with Minikube:



minikube start





---



3. Run Kubescape Scan



Run the scan against your cluster:



kubescape scan framework nsa --format json --output results.json



framework nsa â†’ runs NSA Kubernetes hardening guidelines.



--format json â†’ saves results in JSON.



--output results.json â†’ outputs to a JSON file.







---



4. Sample JSON Output (Excerpt)



Your actual file will be larger, but hereâ€™s a simplified example:



{

  "cluster": "k8s-sec-scan",

  "scannedAt": "2025-08-16T09:30:00Z",

  "results": [

    {

      "controlID": "C-0016",

      "name": "Ensure that the default namespace is not used",

      "severity": "Medium",

      "status": "Failed",

